        <div class="blog-2-headinng-content">
            <p>Tradition is as natural to India as mountains are to Kashmir and beaches are to Mumbai. Just like that ethnic clothing and attire is synonymous to the term &lsquo;India&rsquo;. Ethnic wear is not just a trend, in India the ethnic wear is a way of life. Women and men from diverse distinct backgrounds, from different cohorts all can be spotted all around proudly adorning ethnic wear like vibrant kurtas everywhere! The fusion of ethnic with modern like wearing kurtas with jeans is very popular especially among students and the working population. Some attires like dhoti kurta and sarees are quite often limited only to special occasions like the festival of Diwali or wedding and other ceremonious parties and gatherings. The elegance and charm of draping oneself in the Indian ethnic wear is unbeatable. It is a symbol of pride in our culture while withholding strength that in an immaculate manner holds our cultural values beautifully.</p>
            <p>The festival season is the most favourite time for everyone in the country. Long ques of exuberant shoppers are witnessed with customers going gaga over the trendiest sets, keeping alive the cultural excitement even among the youngest ones in the family. Little girls going to exchange gifts and pleasantries with their mothers in bright and dazzling lehengas, cutely dragging the mud along with their dupattas. Young boys wearing beautiful kurta sets with shiny sandals, waltzing up and down the corridors to flaunt their clothes to friends and family. Young mother with draped sarees on a constant lookout for their young ones as they burn crackers is a sight very common on Diwali.</p>
            <p>Diwali is essentially a time for jazzing up the wardrobes for the most of us. Choosing from the latest trends or the traditional classics, we love to buy new bright and beautiful clothes for the festive season. At Gharobaar, we bring to you the beautiful and intricately handcrafted products from the homes of our producers to yours, packed with love. Choose from the wide collection of products to jazz up your and your family&rsquo;s wardrobe this festive season:</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Saree</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Sarees have always been essentially one of the major part attires displaying our cultures and traditions. Available in possibly every shade imaginable, India boasts of a wide variety of beautifully woven sarees ranging from the cotton and Banarasi sarees of Uttar Pradesh to the silk kanjivaram work traditional to the Kanchipuram region of South India, the bandhini work from the Rajasthan and Gujarat regions along with hand-woven paithini pattern from Maharashtra and pochampally from Orissa among many varieties. Girls and women, brides and widows, all wear sarees at various festivities or celebrations as in India, sarees are not just an attire but a sentiment for many women in India who drape it around proudly. The <a href="https://www.gharobaar.com/women/saris-blouses" class="links-in-blogs">grace and versatility of sarees</a>with doesn&rsquo;t even come close to any traditional attire. Over the years, the variety has also increased drastically leading to better sarees at affordable prices. With the diversity in India in terms of regions, temperatures and weathers, every region has a material, colours and design befitting the suitability and usability. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Suits</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Haute and might, any suit in any color can never go unnoticed, every single variety trending at almost every point of time. In India, suits will never go out of style. Young girls from schools and universities adorn <a href="https://www.gharobaar.com/women/suits-kurtas-sets" class="links-in-blogs">beautiful suit sets</a> even in everyday life as suits are very trendy nowadays with many other varieties coming in the market leading to better options for the consumers. The promotion for ethnic wear, taking pride in our traditions and cultural attire has also helped in increasing the sales. One of the most comfortable form of clothing. Available in various styles from Anarkali to plazo sets and sharara sets, the traditional chikankari of Lucknow or plain cotton salwar and kurta, suits are one of the most beloved traditional Indian attire.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Kurtas</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Kurtas are a delight to wear and are almost ubiquitous nowadays with men, women, young girls and boys all wearing them coupled with beautiful accessories. Kurtas are a night in the shining armour for hot and humid weather given the comfort they offer with loose and wonderful fit. The best part about wearing kurtas is that you can wear these with almost anything- be it jeans, leggings or plazos, etc., all of them looking great. These days with the boom in the influencers on social media, there are tons of videos on Instagram and You Tube that give tutorials on different ways of styling your kurtas. Sales of Kurtas have skyrocketed and thanks to our young population that loves and wears these from biggest occasions to mundane trips to the office or university.</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Indo-western</strong> &ndash;</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Indo-western is essentially fusion of modern and traditional. It is relatively new with collections of kurta dresses, wrap around sarees, etc. coming into the limelight more and more often. Almost everyone loves to wear Indo-western dresses as they hold dearly the traditional cultural touch while keeping up with the latest of the trends in fashion.</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Salwaar kamiz</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>How can Salwaar kamiz slip out of the list of the traditional ethnic wear? Salwaar kamiz has always been in fashion and as has been the trend for decades, it&rsquo;s here only to stay. One of the most fashionable ethnic wear has been the attire Indian women swear by be it for daily wear or the occasional party wear clothing. With the extreme comfort with latest designs and pattern evolving every few years, salwar kameez has got Indian customers hooked!</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Dhoti kurta</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>In the recent years, the traditional attire of dhoti kurta coupled with lungi have taken a center-stage again, replacing the fancy western attire for the great comfort and designs.</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Lehenga</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Lehengas have been an evergreen love of women and girls in India. Be it for the bride, her bridesmaids, for a festival like Diwali, lehengas have maintained their unique charisma in the hearts of the Indian customers in a very beautiful manner. With various material flooding the markets, bright and dazzling lehengas are all the rage!</p>
            <ul class="p-l-0">
                <li><strong>Pathani suits</strong>-</li>
            </ul>
            <p>One of the most loved item by men in India, pathani suits of various colours and designs have got young boys to middle aged men, all hooked completely in their awe.</p>
